不过 大臣阁下 我们可以关闭
However minister, we could always close

62
00:02:56,850 --> 00:02:58,784
你那个政府部门监察办公室
your Bureaucratic Watchdog Office.

63
00:02:58,784 --> 00:03:00,449
这可不行 这才刚刚成立
No, you don't. The office just opened.

64
00:03:00,449 --> 00:03:01,491
这可是我上任以来做的唯一事情
It's the one thing I've done since I got here.

65
00:03:01,491 --> 00:03:03,634
随便您 大臣 不过那早已为人诟病
But as you wish minster, it has been criticised

66
00:03:03,634 --> 00:03:07,049
-被称作好事者的信箱  -我知道
- as a trouble makers' letterbox. - I know.

67
00:03:07,049 --> 00:03:08,750
不过 在选民中倒很受欢迎 Humphrey
It's very popular with the voters Humphrey

68
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,585
这能让我们找到方法
This is a chance to help us find ways

69
00:03:10,585 --> 00:03:12,788
杜绝浪费政府资金
to stop wasting government money.

70
00:03:12,788 --> 00:03:14,340
但是公众对如何挥霍
But public doesn't know anthing about wasting

71
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:16,216
公家的钱财可是一窍不通 我们才是专家
government money. We are the experts.

72
00:03:17,335 --> 00:03:19,126
我可不是这个意思
That's not what I meant.

73
00:03:20,278 --> 00:03:22,822
总之 监察办公室要保留下来
Well, the Bureaucratic Watchdog Office stays.

74
00:03:23,229 --> 00:03:25,710
这样的话 我一时也想不出什么建议了
Well, offhand I can't think of what else to suggest.

75
00:03:25,710 --> 00:03:27,435
你是在认真地跟我说
Are you seriously telling me that

76
00:03:27,435 --> 00:03:29,481
我们没有办法精简人员吗?
there is no way we can cut down?

77
00:03:30,992 --> 00:03:33,151
我想我们可以裁掉一两个端茶小姐
I suppose we could lose one or two of the tea ladies.

78
00:03:33,151 --> 00:03:34,961
别闹了 Humphrey
Oh, Humphrey,

79
00:03:35,151 --> 00:03:37,124
我确实希望你能端正下态度
I do wish you'd take this seriously.

80
00:03:37,124 --> 00:03:39,706
端茶小姐! 我要的是事实
Tea ladies! I want the facts.

81
00:03:39,706 --> 00:03:41,981
我要知道谁在这儿工作 都干些什么工作
I want to know who works here, what they do,

82
00:03:41,981 --> 00:03:43,906
我们有哪些楼 里面的人都在干什么
what buildings we have, what goes on in them.

83
00:03:43,906 --> 00:03:45,405
完整的记录
And complete record.

84
00:03:45,664 --> 00:03:47,148
然后就能知道哪儿该节省开支
Then we'll know where to cut costs,

85
00:03:47,148 --> 00:03:49,435
裁减人员 简化程序了
cut staff, cut procedures...

86
00:03:49,435 --> 00:03:51,018
大臣 行政部门
The Civil Service, Minister,

87
00:03:51,018 --> 00:03:54,260
就是为了贯彻议会颁布的法律而存在的
exists to implement legislation enacted by Parliament.

88
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:56,300
只要议会还在立法
As long as Parliament continues to legislate,

89
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:58,191
行政机构...
the Civil Service...

90
00:03:59,248 --> 00:04:01,705
不过 我完全理解您的要求 大臣
However, I am fully seized of your requirements, minister.

91
00:04:01,705 --> 00:04:04,318
请允许我这就去让轮子转起来
and if you excuse me I'll go and set the wheels in motion.

92
00:04:04,614 --> 00:04:05,403
谢谢
Thank you.

93
00:04:05,438 --> 00:04:06,829
早上好 Weasel先生
Good morning, Mr. Weasel.

94
00:04:06,829 --> 00:04:08,117
Weisel
Weisel.

95
00:04:12,244 --> 00:04:14,163
你知道吗 一个西北地区区长
Did you know that a northwest Regional Controller

96
00:04:14,163 --> 00:04:17,856
仅在他的区域就削减了三千两百万英镑的开支
has achieved cuts of 32 million pounds in his region alone?

97
00:04:19,092 --> 00:04:21,825
而行政机构却把这消息给压了下去
And that the Civil Service is suppressing the whole story?

98
00:04:21,860 --> 00:04:23,755
-真的吗?  -要是真的 就太震惊了
- Is it true? - Well if it is, I'm aghast!

99
00:04:23,755 --> 00:04:24,818
为什么要压制消息?
Why does it suppress news?

100
00:04:24,818 --> 00:04:27,091
因为连他都做得到的话 那别人也不得不节约了
Because if he can save money, everyone else will have to do it.

101
00:04:29,404 --> 00:04:31,358
你何不调查一下
Why don't you look into it,

102
00:04:31,358 --> 00:04:33,400
做个雪貂 四处打探(ferret本意雪貂，引申为打探)
have a bit of a ferret around?

103
00:04:36,326 --> 00:04:37,495
你觉得我可以吗?
Do you think I could?

104
00:04:37,495 --> 00:04:38,578
我觉得主意不错
I think that's a very good idea,

105
00:04:38,578 --> 00:04:40,625
-雪貂 哦不对 Wea…Weisel先生  -嘿！
- Mr. Ferret, er, Weasel. - Hey!

106
00:04:43,752 --> 00:04:45,559
他告诉你是三千二百万英镑?
He told you 32 million pounds?

107
00:04:45,559 --> 00:04:47,033
-是的 Humphrey爵士  -太震惊了
- Yes, Sir Humphrey. - I'm aghast!

108
00:04:47,033 --> 00:04:47,774
我也是
So was I.

109
00:04:47,774 --> 00:04:49,732
我们居然不知道 太不可思议了
It's incredible we didn't know about it.

110
00:04:50,176 --> 00:04:51,488
我早就知道了
I knew about it.

111
00:04:51,581 --> 00:04:52,512
那你为什么震惊?
Then why are you aghast?

112
00:04:52,547 --> 00:04:54,203
我震惊是因为消息泄漏了
I'm aghast that it got out.

113
00:04:55,277 --> 00:04:57,791
明年或许财政部不会给我们那么多钱了
We might get less money from the Treasury next year.

114
00:04:57,791 --> 00:04:59,965
哦 五点半已经过了 来杯雪利酒?
Oh, it's after half past five. Sherry?

115
00:04:59,965 --> 00:05:01,615
呃 嗯 好的 谢谢
Oh, er, yes. Thank you.

116
00:05:02,196 --> 00:05:03,400
你看起来还是很担心 Bernard
You still look worried, Bernard.

117
00:05:03,736 --> 00:05:04,598
嗯 是的
Well... yes.

118
00:05:04,598 --> 00:05:07,425
我的意思是 当然我们想要省钱
I mean, surely we want to save money.

119
00:05:07,425 --> 00:05:09,792
Bernard 你很清楚
Bernard, You know perfectly well

120
00:05:09,792 --> 00:05:10,925
政府部门必定要有
there has to be some way

121
00:05:10,925 --> 00:05:14,045
某种衡量其成就的方法
to measure success in the Civil Service.

122
00:05:15,322 --> 00:05:17,212
英国利兰公司以他们的利润
British Leyland measure their success

123
00:05:17,212 --> 00:05:19,026
来衡量成就
by the size of their profits,

124
00:05:19,026 --> 00:05:20,268
或者 更准确地说
or, to be more accurate,

125
00:05:20,268 --> 00:05:22,886
他们是以自己的损失来衡量失败
they measure their failure by the size of their losses.

126
00:05:23,381 --> 00:05:25,591
我们没有利润 也没有损失
We don't have profits and losses.

127
00:05:25,591 --> 00:05:27,017
我们的成就是靠
We have to measure our success

128
00:05:27,017 --> 00:05:29,586
雇员人数和预算的多少来衡量的
by the size of our staff and our budget.

129
00:05:30,211 --> 00:05:31,847
明白地说 Bernard
By definition, Bernard,

130
00:05:32,278 --> 00:05:34,667
庞大的部门比小部门更有成就
a big department is more successful than a small one.

131
00:05:35,112 --> 00:05:37,631
你是不是说那名西北地区区长
Are you saying that the northwest Regional Controller

132
00:05:37,731 --> 00:05:39,587
省下那么多钱是在做傻事?
boobed by saving so much money?

133
00:05:39,587 --> 00:05:42,188
哦 当然 谁也没让他这么做
Well, of course. Nobody asked him to.

134
00:05:43,182 --> 00:05:44,803
要是人人都如此
Suppose everybody did it!

135
00:05:45,156 --> 00:05:47,307
要是所有人都开始
Suppose everyone went around saving money

136
00:05:47,307 --> 00:05:49,285
不负责任地到处省钱
irresponsibly all over the place.

137
00:05:49,368 --> 00:05:51,722
大臣正有此意 不是吗?
That's what the Minister wants, isn't it?

138
00:05:52,163 --> 00:05:53,507
坐下 Bernard
Do sit down, Bernard.

139
00:05:56,248 --> 00:05:58,703
大臣们就像走马灯更换无常
Ministers come and Ministers go.

140
00:05:59,392 --> 00:06:01,054
任何部门的大臣
The average Minister lasts less

141
00:06:01,054 --> 00:06:02,978
平均任期都不到十一个月
than 11 months in any department.

142
00:06:04,425 --> 00:06:06,252
听着 Bernard 我们责无旁贷地
You see, Bernard, it is our duty

143
00:06:06,252 --> 00:06:09,367
应协助大臣争取部门经费
to assist the Minister to fight for the Department's money

144
00:06:09,367 --> 00:06:11,202
即便他自己担惊受怕
despite his own panic reactions.

145
00:06:11,202 --> 00:06:13,388
你是说帮他克服恐慌
You mean help him overcome his panic.

146
00:06:13,388 --> 00:06:14,922
不 不 不
No. No. No.

147
00:06:14,922 --> 00:06:16,740
我们任他惊慌失措
No, we must let him panic.

148
00:06:16,955 --> 00:06:19,589
政治家乐意惊惶失措 他们需要活动
Politicians like to panic. They need activity.

149
00:06:21,686 --> 00:06:23,710
以此代替成就
It's their substitute for achievement.

150
00:06:25,634 --> 00:06:28,366
我们必须确保一切照旧
We must just ensure that it doesn't change anything.

151
00:06:29,408 --> 00:06:31,989
可他们是民众的代表
But even so they are the people's representatives,

152
00:06:31,989 --> 00:06:33,382
是民主选举的结果
democratically chosen.

153
00:06:33,382 --> 00:06:35,111
议员并非人民的选择
MP's aren't chosen by the people,

154
00:06:35,111 --> 00:06:36,966
而是其所在地党派决定的
they are chosen by their local party.

155
00:06:36,993 --> 00:06:39,135
是由35个穿着邋遢雨衣的男人
35 men in grubby raincoats

156
00:06:39,135 --> 00:06:41,059
或是35个戴着愚蠢礼帽的女人
or 35 women in silly hats.

157
00:06:41,828 --> 00:06:44,573
可内阁成员来自他们中最优秀的人
And the government are selected from the best of them.

158
00:06:44,573 --> 00:06:45,725
Bernard
Bernard,

159
00:06:46,419 --> 00:06:48,735
下院议员仅有630位
there are only 630 MP's.

160
00:06:48,770 --> 00:06:52,368
一个党派超过300名席位便组成内阁
If one party has just over 300 it forms a government.

161
00:06:52,903 --> 00:06:55,831
这300人中 有100名又老又蠢
Of that 300, one hundred are too old and too silly,

162
00:06:55,831 --> 00:06:58,040
还有100名又稚又嫩
one hundred too young and too callow

163
00:06:58,040 --> 00:07:00,641
剩下的大约100名下院议员
which leaves just about a hundred MP's

164
00:07:00,641 --> 00:07:02,765
便填上了100个政府职务
to fill 100 governmental posts.

165
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,122
根本无从挑选
There's no choice at all.

166
00:07:04,157 --> 00:07:06,733
他们未经甄别 未受训练
They've had no selection, no training.

167
00:07:06,733 --> 00:07:09,729
我们不得不为他们代劳
We have to do the job for them.

168
00:07:11,949 --> 00:07:15,145
但节省3千2百万开支的事
But how can we explain saving 32 million pounds

169
00:07:15,145 --> 00:07:16,145
如何向大臣解释?
to the Minister?

170
00:07:16,145 --> 00:07:18,286
我们可以声称
Well, We can explain they've changed

171
00:07:18,286 --> 00:07:20,286
西北的账目体系有了改变
their accounting systems in the northwest.

172
00:07:20,286 --> 00:07:23,184
或者各区的管辖范围经过重新划分
Or that they've redrawn the regional boundaries

173
00:07:23,184 --> 00:07:26,116
现在的数据已经没有意义了
so that the current figures aren't operable.

174
00:07:26,566 --> 00:07:28,051
一切皆有可能
There are all sorts of possibilities.

175
00:07:29,614 --> 00:07:30,838
明白了
I see.

176
00:07:31,957 --> 00:07:33,799
有益的交谈 Bernard
Useful chat, Bernard,

177
00:07:34,643 --> 00:07:36,543
记住这从未发生过
good job it never took place.

178
00:07:38,049 --> 00:07:39,918
是的 当然没有
Yes. Yes. Of course.

179
00:07:39,953 --> 00:07:42,283
我们的朋友Weasel上哪去了?
So what else is our friend Weasel up to?

180
00:07:42,318 --> 00:07:43,794
他在当雪貂
Oh, he's ferretting.

181
00:07:45,352 --> 00:07:47,885
当雪貂? 哪儿?
Ferretting? Where?

182
00:07:47,885 --> 00:07:49,244
四处打探
It's a roving brief.

183
00:07:50,049 --> 00:07:52,895
看来我们不得不给侦查员安排辆政府用车了
Then we shall have to provide Rover with a government car.

184
00:07:53,795 --> 00:07:56,115
便于了解他在哪儿打洞了
So that we'll know where he's digging.

185
00:07:58,139 --> 00:07:59,094
你…
How...

186
00:08:00,145 --> 00:08:02,649
你是如何和谐你的大臣的 小汉?
how are you getting on with your Minister, Humpy?

187
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:05,496
还没把那节约的事控制住?
Got this economising nonsense under control?

188
00:08:05,496 --> 00:08:07,614
是的 控制住了 巨人 或多或少
Yes, I think so, Jumbo... more or less.

189
00:08:08,193 --> 00:08:09,500
“或多或少”什么意思?
What do you mean more or less?

190
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:10,885
好吧 既是又不是
Well... yes and no.

191
00:08:11,888 --> 00:08:15,103
大概与所有其他的政府节约一样吧?
Presumably it's like all the other government economy drives?

192
00:08:15,138 --> 00:08:18,563
三天的新闻发布 三周的内阁备忘录
Three days of press releases, three weeks of ministerial's memos,

193
00:08:18,563 --> 00:08:20,518
中东发生危机 一切恢复正常?
a crisis in the Middle East and back to normal again?

194
00:08:20,518 --> 00:08:22,008
这次稍有不同
Well this one's slightly different.

195
00:08:22,637 --> 00:08:24,175
他想他是要把
I'm afraid He's beginning to see

196
00:08:24,175 --> 00:08:27,359
裁员视为其首要任务了
slimming down the Service as his main task.

197
00:08:27,359 --> 00:08:29,717
该死的 我们无须瘦身!
Dammit, we don't need slimming!

198
00:08:32,957 --> 00:08:35,307
我想你或许应该
I think you might have to conduct

199
00:08:35,307 --> 00:08:37,448
再来一个“自讨苦吃行动”
another Operation Hair Shirt.

200
00:08:38,339 --> 00:08:40,559
自讨苦吃行动
Operation Hair Shirt.

201
00:08:40,899 --> 00:08:42,180
明智的主意
What a good idea.

202
00:08:42,420 --> 00:08:45,709
引领他感受痛苦的个人节约
Guide him towards painful personal economies.

203
00:08:45,709 --> 00:08:47,754
就是这样 你知道
Yes, you know.

204
00:08:48,547 --> 00:08:50,875
“节约应从‘我’做起 大臣阁下”
"Economy begins at home, Minister".

205
00:08:50,875 --> 00:08:52,837
“要树立表率 大臣阁下”
"Set an example, Minister".

206
00:08:52,837 --> 00:08:56,354
“我们必须身体力行才能令人信服 大臣阁下”
"Can't expect others to do what we can't do ourselves, Minister".

207
00:08:56,354 --> 00:09:00,476
对极了 这正是他需要的 自我否定
Yes, yes. Just what he needs, self denial.

208
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:02,407
了不起
Splendid.

209
00:09:05,506 --> 00:09:08,692
好 第3项 节约运动
Right. Item 3. The economy drive.

210
00:09:08,692 --> 00:09:12,033
有关我们的铺张浪费 Frank 提供了
Frank has come up with some really startling indications

211
00:09:12,033 --> 00:09:13,781
一些让人震惊的信息
of wastage in our very midst.

212
00:09:13,816 --> 00:09:14,877
他核实过了?
Has he confirmed?

213
00:09:14,877 --> 00:09:17,400
我想我揭露的事实准会让你大吃一惊的
And I think you gonna be pretty surprised of what I uncovered

214
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,651
我得说 Humphrey
And I must say Hamphrey

215
00:09:18,751 --> 00:09:20,541
这些事实看来是对
These facts are a frightening indictment

216
00:09:20,541 --> 00:09:22,730
官僚作风与自我放纵的可怕谴责
of bureaucratic sloppiness and self indulgence.

217
00:09:22,730 --> 00:09:23,618
天哪 天哪
Dear, yeah.

218
00:09:23,618 --> 00:09:24,825
但如你所见
But as you'll see,

219
00:09:25,107 --> 00:09:27,056
这倒是给我们提供了巨大的空间
they do give us enormous scope

220
00:09:27,056 --> 00:09:29,177
来大刀阔斧地开展节约运动
for some really dramatic economies.

221
00:09:29,792 --> 00:09:30,620
令人期待!
Good show!

222
00:09:31,656 --> 00:09:35,726
两份报告 一份关于人力资源 一份办公楼
Two files, one on manpower, one on buildings.

223
00:09:36,230 --> 00:09:37,890
从办公楼开始吧
Let's start with the buildings.

224
00:09:39,241 --> 00:09:41,680
Chadwick大厦 西Audley街
Chadwick House, West Audley Street.

225
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:43,967
巨大的建筑 但办公的人却寥寥无几
A huge building only a handful of people working there.

226
00:09:43,967 --> 00:09:44,559
是啊 20人
Yes, 20...

227
00:09:44,594 --> 00:09:47,355
抱歉 我恰好清楚Chadwick大厦的情况
I'm so sorry. I do happen to know about Chadwick House.

228
00:09:47,355 --> 00:09:48,496
你了解些什么?
What do you know?

229
00:09:48,496 --> 00:09:50,144
很显然并未充分利用
It's obviously underused at the most,

230
00:09:50,144 --> 00:09:51,400
但它已被指定为
but it's the destinite office

231
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:53,716
新成立的环境署办公楼
for the new Commission for the Environment.

232
00:09:53,716 --> 00:09:55,040
我们还说不准它是否
And we're actually wondering

233
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:57,772
足够容纳所有的工作人员
if it's going to be big enough for all the staff.

234
00:09:59,061 --> 00:10:00,240
好吧
O.K.

235
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:03,135
那么位于Walthamstow的Ladysmith大厦呢?
What about Ladysmith Buildings, Walthamstow.

236
00:10:03,135 --> 00:10:05,500
-那可是完全空着  -理应如此
- Apparently that's empty. - Of course.

237
00:10:06,011 --> 00:10:07,678
你的“理应如此”的意思是?
What do you mean, of course?

238
00:10:07,680 --> 00:10:10,504
出于安全考虑 大臣 我不能多言
Security, minister. I can say no more.

239
00:10:14,024 --> 00:10:16,000
你是指军情六处?
Do you mean MI6?

240
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:21,000
这又是什么意思?
What's that supposed to mean?

241
00:10:21,225 --> 00:10:23,959
我们不承认有军情六处这回事
We do not admit that MI6 exists.

242
00:10:23,959 --> 00:10:25,100
谁不知道它的存在
Everybody knows it exists.

243
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:26,960
即便如此 我们不能承认
Nevertheless, we do not admit it.

244
00:10:26,961 --> 00:10:30,375
这桌子旁坐着的人并非都是经过检疫的
Not everyone round this table has been vetted.

245
00:10:31,616 --> 00:10:33,111
对猫才用“检疫”这个词吧
I thought that was something you do cats.

246
00:10:36,058 --> 00:10:38,606
确实如此 对“雪貂”就不用 大臣阁下
Yes, indeed. But not ferrets, Minister.

247
00:10:41,642 --> 00:10:44,177
Ladysmith大厦是最高机密
Ladysmith House is top secret.

248
00:10:44,614 --> 00:10:47,864
Walthamstow上七层的大厦怎么会是最高机密?
How can a seven-storey building in Walthamstow to be top secret?

249
00:10:49,531 --> 00:10:51,465
有志者事竟成
Where there's a will there's a way.

250
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:54,655
那Wellington大厦和Westminster旧厅呢?
What about Wellington House and Westminster Old Hall?

251
00:10:54,655 --> 00:10:56,126
Wellington大厦 位于Hyde公园大道
Wellington House, Hyde Park Road,

252
00:10:56,126 --> 00:10:58,762
价值七百五十万英镑
estimated value 7.5 million pounds.

253
00:10:58,762 --> 00:11:00,790
Westminster旧厅 位于Sackville广场
Westminster Old Hall, Sackville Square,

254
00:11:00,790 --> 00:11:03,349
价值一千一百万英镑
estimated value 11 million pounds.

255
00:11:03,349 --> 00:11:04,887
两幢办公楼里的员工都不多
Each building with a tiny staff,

256
00:11:04,887 --> 00:11:07,920
却都摆满了档案柜
and both filled apparently entirely with filing cabinets.

257
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:10,386
请问这些估价的根据是?
May I ask the source of these valuations?

258
00:11:10,386 --> 00:11:12,132
办公用房的市价
Going rate for office property in the end.

259
00:11:12,132 --> 00:11:14,938
但它们没一个能卖到这个现行价格
But neither of these properties would fetch the going rate.

260
00:11:14,973 --> 00:11:15,606
为什么不能?
Why not?

261
00:11:15,606 --> 00:11:18,041
Wellington大厦既没有防火梯 也没有防火门
Wellington House has no fire escape or fire doors

262
00:11:18,041 --> 00:11:20,753
而大厦的构造也不容改建
and the fabric of building wouldn't stand the alteration.

263
00:11:20,753 --> 00:11:22,220
不能当作办公楼
so it can't be used as offices.

264
00:11:22,220 --> 00:11:23,790
-那你是如何用上这幢大厦的?  -是啊
- How are you able to use them? - Yeah?

265
00:11:23,790 --> 00:11:26,978
政府办公楼无须防火安全通道
Government buildings do not require fire safety clearance.

266
00:11:27,544 --> 00:11:28,386
为何不用?
Why not?

267
00:11:28,586 --> 00:11:31,990
可能是女王陛下的公仆们
Well, perhaps because Her Majesty's Civil Servants

268
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,869
不易着火吧
are not easily inflamed.

269
00:11:35,575 --> 00:11:36,795
希望如此
I hope it is right.

270
00:11:38,649 --> 00:11:40,006
那Westminster旧厅呢?
What about Westminster Old Hall?

271
00:11:40,699 --> 00:11:42,876
一级保护建筑
Class one Registered Building.

272
00:11:42,876 --> 00:11:45,338
不能改变当前房屋使用人
Can't change current user designation.

273
00:11:47,214 --> 00:11:49,734
好吧 Beaconsfield街上的3到17号大楼呢?
I see. 3 to 17 Beaconsfield Street?

274
00:11:49,734 --> 00:11:52,044
对 是了 该建筑现在有了三层的
Ah, yes. Now that has a three-level

275
00:11:52,044 --> 00:11:54,559
钢筋混凝土地下室
reinforced concrete basement.

276
00:11:55,184 --> 00:11:56,093
这又怎么了?
So?

277
00:11:56,093 --> 00:11:58,056
防范未然
It is there in case.

278
00:11:58,949 --> 00:11:59,875
未然什么?
In case?

279
00:12:00,075 --> 00:12:01,725
要知道 大臣阁下
Well, you know, Minister.

280
00:12:01,725 --> 00:12:04,397
政府应急总部所在地 以防万一
Emergency Government Headquarters, if and when.

281
00:12:04,397 --> 00:12:05,274
万一怎么了?
If and when what?

282
00:12:06,762 --> 00:12:09,582
万一... 你明白的
If and when... you know what.

283
00:12:09,582 --> 00:12:10,621
什么?
What?

284
00:12:11,526 --> 00:12:13,120
你明白的那个万一
If and when you know what.

285
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,802
我不明白 是什么?
I don't know what. What?

286
00:12:15,411 --> 00:12:15,929
什么
What?

287
00:12:15,964 --> 00:12:17,666
你那句“你明白的那个万一”是什么意思?
What do you mean, if and when you know what?

288
00:12:18,093 --> 00:12:19,529
大臣 万一危机来临
Minister, when the chips are down,

289
00:12:19,529 --> 00:12:21,953
局势动荡 吹灯拔蜡…
and the balloons are up and the lights go out...

290
00:12:24,229 --> 00:12:26,482
政府也得有个地方继续运行啊
There has to be somewhere to carry on government,

291
00:12:26,482 --> 00:12:28,663
即便一切都陷入瘫痪
even if everything else stops.

292
00:12:29,358 --> 00:12:30,373
为什么?
Why?

293
00:12:31,791 --> 00:12:33,791
难道国家分崩离析了
The government just stops just because

294
00:12:33,791 --> 00:12:35,888
内阁就该偃旗息鼓吗?
the whole country's been destroyed.

295
00:12:38,794 --> 00:12:40,526
毁于一旦已经够糟了
Annihilation's bad enough,

296
00:12:40,526 --> 00:12:42,999
无政府状态只会雪上加霜
without anarchy to make things even worse.

297
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:45,890
你以为尚有许多反叛的余孽?
you mean a lot of rebellions cinders?

298
00:12:48,048 --> 00:12:49,048
没错
That's right.

299
00:12:49,083 --> 00:12:50,659
到那时你还指望管理谁?
Who would be there for you to govern?

300
00:12:50,659 --> 00:12:53,902
肯定还会有些普通民众
Well, abound to be some ordinary people around.

301
00:12:54,459 --> 00:12:56,220
那中央户籍登记处的那幢楼呢?
What about central registry?

302
00:12:56,391 --> 00:12:57,680
没有建筑许可
No planning permission.

303
00:12:57,702 --> 00:12:59,320
他怎么什么都知道?
How did he know all these?

304
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:01,043
你早就知道我去哪儿了?
You knew where I'd been.

305
00:13:01,043 --> 00:13:02,930
我们当然知道他何去何从
Obviously we knew where he'd been.

306
00:13:02,965 --> 00:13:04,580
难不成他本该暗中打探吗?
Why, was he supposed to be spying?

307
00:13:05,283 --> 00:13:07,518
我们信奉公开调查 不是吗?
We do believe in open enquiries, don't we?

308
00:13:09,704 --> 00:13:12,092
我们看看人力资源方面
Let us turn to manpower.

309
00:13:12,424 --> 00:13:13,431
对 我们看看
Yes, let's!

310
00:13:14,562 --> 00:13:16,691
在Sunderland就有90名公务员
Aparently there are 90 Civil Servants

311
00:13:16,691 --> 00:13:18,726
明显在重复白厅这儿
in Sunderland except the duplicating the work

312
00:13:18,726 --> 00:13:20,238
另外90个人从事的工作
of 90 more here in WhiteHall.

313
00:13:20,238 --> 00:13:22,698
这源于内阁的一项决定
That stems from a Cabinet decision,

314
00:13:22,698 --> 00:13:25,493
-为东北地区创造就业机会  -把这些人裁了吧
- job creation in the northeast. - Well let's get rid of them.

315
00:13:25,528 --> 00:13:28,065
对 一下子就裁掉了90名公务员
Yes, we'd get rid of 90 Civil Servants at a stroke.

316
00:13:28,065 --> 00:13:31,624
-是啊 或是一下子就引起了一场罢工  -对 什么?
- Yes, or indeed, at a strike. - Yes. What?

317
00:13:31,933 --> 00:13:34,407
个人而言 我完全
Well, personally I would be whole heartily

318
00:13:34,407 --> 00:13:36,165
赞成这个行动 大臣阁下
in favour of such a move, minister.

319
00:13:36,165 --> 00:13:37,639
这会是一场辉煌的节约运动
It would be a splendid economy.

320
00:13:37,639 --> 00:13:41,557
在一个萧条的边缘选区裁员
And show great political courage to sack staff

321
00:13:41,557 --> 00:13:44,693
会展现出极大的政治魄力
in depressed marginal constituencies.

322
00:13:47,087 --> 00:13:48,520
我就是不信
I just don't believe it that

323
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:51,410
没有可节约之处 浪费明明随处可见
There is nowhere we can cut down. I see waste everywhere.

324
00:13:51,410 --> 00:13:52,680
我同意您的话 大臣阁下
Well I agree with you, Minister.

325
00:13:52,710 --> 00:13:54,040
确有可节约之处
There's certain diseconomy

326
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:55,082
好吧 哪儿?
Well, where?

327
00:13:55,778 --> 00:13:58,300
我有时会觉得恰恰是
Well. I sometimes feel that the very way

328
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:00,987
我们的行事排场太过奢侈
we do things is on too lavish a scale.

329
00:14:00,987 --> 00:14:02,767
您知道 汽车 办公器材
You know, cars, furnishings...

330
00:14:02,767 --> 00:14:06,248
娱乐设备 私人办公人员 复印机…
entertainments, private office staff, duplicating machines...

331
00:14:06,283 --> 00:14:07,975
对 对 对 好极了
Yes. Yes. Yes. Fine. Yes.

332
00:14:07,975 --> 00:14:10,080
我们就从这下手 这可太妙了
That's where we'll start. Magnificent.

333
00:14:10,098 --> 00:14:12,622
-不过 这里还有个问题  -我就知道
- Yes, unfortunely there is a difficulty. - I knew it!

334
00:14:12,622 --> 00:14:15,034
是啊 如果上头的人还继续享受
Yes, it does cause profound resentment

335
00:14:15,034 --> 00:14:17,000
各种便利和舒适
if those at the top continue to enjoy

336
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,509
却不让下面的人分享
the comforts, the conveniences,

337
00:14:18,509 --> 00:14:20,464
势必会引起强烈的不满
they withdraw from those below them,

338
00:14:20,464 --> 00:14:23,130
更不必说公众舆论导致的可怕后果
not to mention the deeply damaging publicity...

339
00:14:23,743 --> 00:14:26,555
你是说我和你应该…
You mean you and I should...

340
00:14:26,555 --> 00:14:28,320
以身作则?
Set a personal example?

341
00:14:28,476 --> 00:14:30,289
节约应从“我”做起?
Economy begins at home?

342
00:14:30,289 --> 00:14:31,549
我们必须身体力行
We can't expect others to do

343
00:14:31,549 --> 00:14:33,825
才能令人信服 不是吗?
what we don't do ourselves, can we?

344
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,600
靠这个好像省不出多少吧?
Does it really save all that much?

345
00:14:36,610 --> 00:14:38,266
当然不会直接省下来
Well, not directly, no.

346
00:14:38,266 --> 00:14:43,379
但对整个政府部门的模范作用将不可限量
but as an example to the whole public service incalculable.

347
00:14:43,379 --> 00:14:44,581
好吧 不知道...
Well, I don't know...

348
00:14:44,581 --> 00:14:48,520
你想 Jim 这会产生巨大的公众效应
You know, Jim, there'd be a lot of great publicity in it:

349
00:14:49,344 --> 00:14:51,154
“大臣指明了方向”
"The Minister shows the way".

350
00:14:51,975 --> 00:14:53,556
“清廉的内阁”
"Slimline Government".

351
00:14:53,556 --> 00:14:54,943
“哈克作出了表率”
"Hacker sets an example".

352
00:14:54,943 --> 00:14:56,754
Jim号召“节约”
"Save it" says Jim.

353
