00:22:47,645 --> 00:22:49,891
当然 在通常情况下...
Of course, in normal circumstances...

534
00:22:49,891 --> 00:22:51,594
好了 好了 知道了 知道了
Yes. Yes. I know, I know.

535
00:22:52,712 --> 00:22:54,875
恕我提醒 您和您夫人8点要出席
Would you mind if I remind you. You and Mrs. Hacker are due

536
00:22:54,875 --> 00:22:56,215
法国大使馆的招待会
at the French Embassy at 8 o'clock.

537
00:22:56,710 --> 00:22:59,718
对 帮我备车好吗?
Oh, yes. Get me the car, will you?

538
00:23:02,870 --> 00:23:04,331
最好先给我夫人打个电话
Oh... Better ring Mrs. Hacker,

539
00:23:04,331 --> 00:23:06,122
让她开我们的车进城
ask her to bring our car into town.

540
00:23:06,122 --> 00:23:08,199
恐怕无法如您所愿 大臣
Well I have to explore the possibility, minister.

541
00:23:08,199 --> 00:23:10,397
您夫人说将它放在修车厂修理了
Mrs. Hacker said she had dropped it off at the garage.

542
00:23:10,397 --> 00:23:12,322
她就不能明天再修吗
She'll have to do that tomorrow.

543
00:23:12,322 --> 00:23:15,098
它可以把我们送至Kensington
It'll get us as far as Kensington anyway.

544
00:23:15,545 --> 00:23:17,341
至少这不成问题
At least there are no problems about that.

545
00:23:29,028 --> 00:23:31,690
Annie 不妙 我们必须步行
Annie, it's no good. We'll have to walk.

546
00:23:32,114 --> 00:23:33,194
你带伞了吗?
Have you got the umbrella?

547
00:23:33,194 --> 00:23:34,225
没 你呢?
No, haven't you?

548
00:23:35,186 --> 00:23:36,753
这下好了
Terrific.

549
00:23:43,847 --> 00:23:45,035
你走错方向了
You're going the wrong way.

550
00:23:45,340 --> 00:23:47,571
没有 我是要回家
I'm not, I'm going home.

551
00:23:50,603 --> 00:23:52,642
Annie 我知道这是什么问题了
Annie! I think I've found what's wrong.

552
00:23:52,642 --> 00:23:54,017
我早就知道了
I know I have!

553
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:05,017
(法国大使馆)


554
00:24:11,516 --> 00:24:12,542
先生 有何贵干?
Oui, Monsieur?

555
00:24:12,542 --> 00:24:15,291
女皇任命的行政大臣
Her Majesty's Minister for Administrative Affairs.

556
00:24:18,935 --> 00:24:20,624
我的车坏了
My car broke down.

557
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:26,267
Hacker先生 看来您需要喝点香槟
Mr. Hacker, you look as if you need some champagne.

558
00:24:26,267 --> 00:24:28,291
是的 大量
I do. Lots!

559
00:25:33,217 --> 00:25:34,230
Hacker先生?
Mr. Hacker?

560
00:25:38,972 --> 00:25:40,121
谢了 老兄
Thanks, mate.

561
00:25:43,286 --> 00:25:44,419
黄色小报
Gutter press!

562
00:25:50,707 --> 00:25:52,863
好吧 上面写了什么?
All right, what do they say?

563
00:25:53,840 --> 00:25:57,737
“节约大师香槟酒会后醉卧排水沟”
Mr. Economy falls down in gutter after champagne party".

564
00:25:57,737 --> 00:25:59,955
-老天  -这个好点
- Oh, my God! - This one is better.

565
00:25:59,955 --> 00:26:02,881
“哈克在大使招待会后疲惫不堪 情绪失控”
"Hacker tired and emotional after Embassy reception".

566
00:26:02,881 --> 00:26:05,270
-这叫好点?  -至少有些不同
- Is that better? - It's different.

567
00:26:06,913 --> 00:26:08,435
有没有谁说过任何
Do any of them say anything

568
00:26:08,435 --> 00:26:10,306
“疲惫不堪 情绪失控”之外的话?
other than "tired and emotional"?

569
00:26:10,306 --> 00:26:12,730
William·Hickey说您过度兴奋 大臣阁下
William Hickey said you were overwrought, Minister.

570
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:14,021
只是“过度兴奋”?
Just "overwrought"?

571
00:26:14,056 --> 00:26:15,243
没有提到醉酒?
Nothing about being drunk?

572
00:26:15,243 --> 00:26:16,391
只有“过度兴奋”
Just "overwrought".

573
00:26:16,391 --> 00:26:18,978
原话其实是“过度兴奋如同笨蛋”
"Overwrought as a newt", actually.

574
00:26:20,967 --> 00:26:22,816
还能有比这更糟吗 还有吗?
It couldn't really be any worse. Could they?

575
00:26:22,864 --> 00:26:25,101
我不想打击您 大臣
I don't want to depress you, minister...

576
00:26:25,101 --> 00:26:27,811
但“泰晤士报”上有个头版报道
but there is just this lead story in The Times.

577
00:26:29,027 --> 00:26:29,989
的确更糟!
It is worse!

578
00:26:30,221 --> 00:26:32,982
“哈克征募了400名新公务员
"Hacker recruit 400 new Civil Servants in,

579
00:26:32,982 --> 00:26:34,680
在其‘节约运动’期间”
quote, 'economy drive'"!

580
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:37,457
-增加400名公务员?  -大臣 您吩咐用他们
- 400 more Civil Servants? - Minister, You asked for them.

581
00:26:37,457 --> 00:26:40,632
您要求彻底的研究 收集事实和数据
You demanded a complete study and survey, facts and figures.

582
00:26:40,632 --> 00:26:43,043
这些措施得有人手才行
These measures cannot be taken with none people.

583
00:26:43,043 --> 00:26:46,197
你想出了额外的工作 就必须雇佣更多的人手
You create more jobs. More people have to be employed to do it.

584
00:26:46,197 --> 00:26:47,630
这是常识而已
It's common sense.

585
00:26:47,630 --> 00:26:50,897
如果您还坚持落实政府部门监察办公室
If you persist with the Bureaucratic Watchdog Office,

586
00:26:51,354 --> 00:26:54,139
那就至少还要再添400个新职位
there'll be another 400 new jobs there as well.

587
00:26:57,220 --> 00:26:59,278
-我们该如何是好?  -大臣阁下
- What are we going to do? - Well, Minister...

588
00:27:00,742 --> 00:27:02,669
如果我们停止节约运动
If we were to end the economy drive

589
00:27:02,669 --> 00:27:05,280
关闭政府部门监察办公室
and close the Bureaucratic Watchdog Office,

590
00:27:05,280 --> 00:27:07,571
我们可以立即发布新闻通告
we could issue an immediate press announcement

591
00:27:07,571 --> 00:27:09,035
说您砍掉了800个职位
that you'd axed 800 jobs.

592
00:27:09,035 --> 00:27:12,914
现在您只需瞟一眼这份草拟的提案
Now, if you'd care to glance at this draft proposal...

593
00:27:12,914 --> 00:27:15,784
但没人担任过这些职位啊 还没任命过谁呢
But nobody's doing those jobs. Nobody has been recruited yet.

594
00:27:15,784 --> 00:27:17,102
这样节约就更为可观
And even greater economy,

595
00:27:17,102 --> 00:27:19,902
我们还节省了800份裁员费
we've saved 800 redundancy payments as well.

596
00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:22,700
那是造假
That's foully

597
00:27:22,700 --> 00:27:25,140
是谎言 是虚伪 是...
it's cheated, it's dishonest, it's just...

598
00:27:25,140 --> 00:27:27,668
玩数字游戏 蒙蔽他人的耳目而已
cheating with figures, pulling the wool over people's eyes.

599
00:27:27,703 --> 00:27:30,800
-事实上是政府发布的新闻  -好吧
- A Government Press release, in fact. - Fine.

600
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:34,552
可我们到底该怎样做才能精简行政部门呢?
What do we actually going to do to slim down the Civil Service?

601
00:27:34,552 --> 00:27:39,016
大臣 或许您可以过目一下这份焕然一新的提案
Minister, after you get announce at this entirely fresh proposal.

602
00:27:41,838 --> 00:27:43,886
“提议辞退一二名
"Proposal for the Reduction of the Number of

603
00:27:45,149 --> 00:27:46,675
端茶小姐”
Tea Ladies".

